law.text:
The Commissioner may adopt regulations about long-term care insurance with respect to:
form and content of disclosures;
terms of renewals;
initial and subsequent conditions of eligibility;
nonduplication of coverage provisions;
preexisting conditions;
renewability of coverage;
continuation and conversion;
probationary periods, limitation of coverage provisions, and recurrent conditions;
coverage of dependents;
loss ratio standards; and
any other matter that the Commissioner determines is in the best interest of the public.
